  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The importance of multimodal analgesia for postoperative pain management is well known and
      regional anesthesia techniques are commonly prefferred to provide better analgesia. Erector
      spinae plane block (ESB) is a new defined and effective regional anesthesia technique. But
      two injections can be unconfortable for some patients. With this study, we aimed to compare
      the analgesia effect of bilateral and unilateral ESP block for laparoscopic cholecystectomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
